Zuppa di verdura is a delicious Italian vegetable soup that's hearty and perfect for any season. Here's a basic recipe to get you started:

Ingredients:
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 onion, finely chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
2 carrots, peeled and diced
2 celery stalks, diced
1 zucchini, diced
1 potato, peeled and diced
1 cup green beans, trimmed and cut into pieces
1 cup spinach or kale, chopped
1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes (optional)
4 cups vegetable broth
1 teaspoon dried thyme
1 teaspoon dried basil
Salt and pepper to taste
Grated Parmesan cheese (optional, for serving)
Crusty bread (optional, for serving)
Instructions:
Heat the Oil: In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat the olive oil over medium heat.

Saut√© the Aromatics: Add the chopped onion and garlic, and cook until the onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.

Cook the Vegetables: Add the carrots and celery. Cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Add Potatoes and Beans: Stir in the diced potato and green beans, and cook for another 5 minutes.

Add Zucchini and Tomatoes (if using): Stir in the diced zucchini and the canned tomatoes (if using). Cook for an additional 5 minutes.
Add Broth and Seasonings: Pour in the vegetable broth and add the dried thyme and basil. Bring the soup to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer.

Simmer: Let the soup simmer for about 20-30 minutes, or until all the vegetables are tender.

Add Greens: Stir in the chopped spinach or kale and cook for another 5 minutes until the greens are wilted.

Season: Taste the soup and adjust the seasoning with salt and pepper as needed.

Serve: Ladle the soup into bowls and, if desired, sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Serve with crusty bread on the side.

Tips:
Variety: Feel free to customize the soup with whatever vegetables you have on hand. Leeks, cabbage, or peas can be great additions.
Beans: For added protein, you can add a can of cannellini beans or chickpeas.
Creamy Version: For a creamy version, blend part or all of the soup with an immersion blender.
Enjoy your zuppa di verdura!